76: 
77: ## Quick Start with Docker
78: 
79: ### 1. Clone the repository
80: 
81: ```bash
82: git clone <repository-url>
83: cd <project-root>
84: ```
85: 
86: ### 2. Configure environment variables
87: 
88: ```bash
89: # Create a .env file in the devops/ directory
90: cp devops/.env.example devops/.env
91: 
92: # Or create manually:
93: cat > devops/.env << 'EOF'
94: SECRET_KEY=your-super-secret-key-change-this
95: DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./data/todo.db
96: ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30
97: ALGORITHM=HS256
98: EOF
99: ```
100: 
101: ### 3. Build and start all services
102: 
103: ```bash
104: cd devops
105: docker compose up --build -d
106: ```
107: 
108: ### 4. Verify services are running
109: 
110: ```bash
111: # Check container status
112: docker compose ps
113: 
114: # Backend health check
115: curl http://localhost:8000/health
116: 
117: # Frontend health check
118: curl http://localhost:3000
119: ```
120: 
121: ### 5. Access the application
122: 
123: | Service          | URL                          |
124: |------------------|------------------------------|
125: | Frontend (React) | http://localhost:3000         |
126: | Backend API      | http://localhost:8000/api/    |
127: | Swagger Docs     | http://localhost:8000/docs    |
128: | ReDoc            | http://localhost:8000/redoc   |
129: 
130: ### 6. Stop all services
131: 
132: ```bash
133: cd devops
134: docker compose down
135: 
136: # To also remove volumes (database data):
137: docker compose down -v
138: ```
139: 
140: ---
141: 
142: ## Manual Setup (Development)
143: 
144: ### Backend Setup
145: 
146: ```bash
147: # 1. Create and activate virtual environment
148: python -m venv venv
149: 
150: # On Linux/macOS:
151: source venv/bin/activate
152: # On Windows:
153: venv\Scripts\activate
154: 
155: # 2. Install dependencies
156: pip install --upgrade pip
157: pip install -r devops/requirements.txt
158: 
159: # 3. Set environment variables
160: export SECRET_KEY="dev-secret-key"
161: export DATABASE_URL="sqlite:///./todo.db"
162: export ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30
163: export ALGORITHM="HS256"
164: 
165: # 4. Run the backend server
166: cd src/backend
167: uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
168: ```
169: 
170: The backend will be available at http://localhost:8000
171: Swagger docs at http://localhost:8000/docs
172: 
173: ### Frontend Setup
174: 
175: ```bash
176: # 1. Navigate to frontend directory
177: cd src/frontend
178: 
179: # 2. Install dependencies
180: npm install
181: 
182: # 3. Start Vite development server
183: npm run dev
184: ```
185: 
186: The frontend will be available at http://localhost:3000
187: Vite proxy is configured to forward `/api` requests to `http://localhost:8000`.
188: 
189: ---
190: 
191: ## Running Tests
192: 
193: ### Backend Tests
194: 
195: ```bash
196: # Activate virtual environment first
197: source venv/bin/activate  # or venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
198: 
199: # Install test dependencies
200: pip install -r devops/requirements.txt
201: 
202: # Run all backend tests from project root
203: cd src/backend
204: python -m pytest ../../tests/backend/ -v
205: 
206: # Run with coverage report
207: python -m pytest ../../tests/backend/ -v --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing --cov-report=html
208: 
209: # View HTML coverage report
210: open htmlcov/index.html  # macOS
211: xdg-open htmlcov/index.html  # Linux
212: start htmlcov/index.html  # Windows
213: ```
214: 
215: ### Frontend Tests
216: 
217: ```bash
218: cd src/frontend
219: 
220: # Run tests (if test runner is configured)
221: npm test
222: ```
223: 
224: > Note: The frontend currently uses Vite without a test runner configured.
225: > To add testing, install vitest: `npm install -D vitest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom`
226: 
227: ### Run All Tests via Docker
228: 
229: ```bash
230: # Backend tests in container
231: docker compose -f devops/docker-compose.yml run --rm backend \
232:   python -m pytest /app/tests/ -v --cov=/app/app --cov-report=term-missing
233: ```
234: 
235: ---
236: 
237: ## CI/CD Pipeline
238: 
239: The CI/CD pipeline is defined in `devops/.github/workflows/ci.yml` and runs on GitHub Actions.
240: 
241: ### Pipeline Stages
242: 
243: 1. **Backend Tests** — Installs Python deps, runs pytest with coverage
244: 2. **Frontend Build** — Installs Node deps, builds production bundle with Vite
245: 3. **Docker Build** — Builds both Docker images and tests docker-compose startup
246: 
247: ### Triggers
248: 
249: - **Push** to `main` or `develop` branches
250: - **Pull requests** targeting `main`
251: 
252: ### To use the CI pipeline:
253: 
254: ```bash
255: # Copy the workflow file to your repo root
256: mkdir -p .github/workflows
257: cp devops/.github/workflows/ci.yml .github/workflows/ci.yml
258: 
259: # Commit and push
260: git add .github/workflows/ci.yml
261: git commit -m "Add CI/CD pipeline"
262: git push origin main
263: ```
264: 
265: ---
266: 
267: ## Environment Variables
268: 
269: | Variable                     | Description                        | Default                              | Required |
270: |------------------------------|------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|----------|
271: | `SECRET_KEY`                 | JWT signing secret key             | `super-secret-key-change-in-production` | Yes      |
272: | `DATABASE_URL`               | SQLite connection string           | `sqlite:///./todo.db`                | Yes      |
273: | `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES`| JWT token expiration in minutes    | `30`                                 | No       |
274: | `ALGORITHM`                  | JWT signing algorithm              | `HS256`                              | No       |
275: 
276: ---
277: 
278: ## API Documentation
279: 
280: Once the backend is running, interactive API documentation is available:
281: 
282: - **Swagger UI**: http://localhost:8000/docs
283: - **ReDoc**: http://localhost:8000/redoc
284: - **OpenAPI JSON**: http://localhost:8000/openapi.json
285: 
286: ### Key API Endpoints
287: 
288: | Method | Endpoint              | Description                  | Auth Required |
289: |--------|-----------------------|------------------------------|---------------|
290: | POST   | `/api/auth/register`  | Register a new user          | No            |
291: | POST   | `/api/auth/login`     | Login and get JWT token      | No            |
292: | GET    | `/api/auth/me`        | Get current user profile     | Yes           |
293: | GET    | `/api/tasks/`         | List all tasks (filterable)  | Yes           |
294: | POST   | `/api/tasks/`         | Create a new task            | Yes           |
295: | GET    | `/api/tasks/{id}`     | Get task by ID               | Yes           |
296: | PUT    | `/api/tasks/{id}`     | Update a task                | Yes           |
297: | DELETE | `/api/tasks/{id}`     | Delete a task                | Yes           |
298: | GET    | `/api/dashboard/`     | Dashboard summary            | Yes           |
299: | GET    | `/health`             | Health check                 | No            |
300: 
301: ### Task Filters (query parameters on GET /api/tasks/)
302: 
303: - `status` — Filter by status (`todo`, `in_progress`, `done`, `cancelled`)
304: - `priority` — Filter by priority (`low`, `medium`, `high`, `urgent`)
305: - `due_before` — Filter tasks due before a date (ISO format)
306: - `due_after` — Filter tasks due after a date (ISO format)
307: - `search` — Search in title and description
308: 
309: ---
310: 
311: ## Troubleshooting
312: 
313: ### Port already in use
314: 
315: ```bash
316: # Find and kill process on port 8000
317: lsof -ti:8000 | xargs kill -9
318: 
319: # Or change ports in docker-compose.yml
320: ```
321: 
322: ### Database reset
323: 
324: ```bash
325: # Remove SQLite database
326: rm -f src/backend/todo.db
327: 
328: # Or with Docker volumes
329: docker compose -f devops/docker-compose.yml down -v
330: ```
331: 
332: ### Rebuild containers from scratch
333: 
334: ```bash
335: cd devops
336: docker compose down -v --rmi all
337: docker compose up --build -d
338: ```
