LAlchemy) + React + JWT.", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:07:14.866429"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "New file available: output/architecture/c4_components.md", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:07:37.293206"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/nginx.conf", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:08:55.879006"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "New file available: output/shared_dependencies.json", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:08:58.444237"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/docker-compose.yml", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:10:43.257753"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "New file available: output/architecture/architecture_overview.md", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:11:05.373971"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "Architecture and shared_dependencies.json are ready. Check blackboard keys 'architecture' and 'shared_dependencies'. Full file structure, API contracts, models, schemas, services, and security specs are defined in output/shared_dependencies.json. You can start coding.", "urgent": true, "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:12:09.991574"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/.github/workflows/ci.yml", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:12:25.115366"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "Architecture is complete! Key files for you:\n\n1. **output/shared_dependencies.json** - Complete interface contracts with all file structures, models, schemas, API endpoints, services, and security functions.\n\n2. **output/architecture/c4_components.md** - Detailed component diagram showing all backend and frontend components.\n\n3. **Backend structure**: app/main.py, app/config.py, app/database.py, app/models/{user,task}.py, app/schemas/{user,task,token}.py, app/routers/{auth,tasks,health}.py, app/services/{auth_service,task_service}.py, app/core/{security,dependencies}.py\n\n4. **Frontend structure**: src/main.jsx, src/App.jsx, src/api/{client,auth,tasks}.js, src/context/AuthContext.jsx, src/hooks/useTasks.js, src/pages/{LoginPage,RegisterPage,DashboardPage}.jsx, src/components/{TaskList,TaskCard,TaskForm,TaskFilter,ProtectedRoute,Navbar}.jsx\n\nIMPORTANT: Please use class-based services (AuthService, TaskService) as defined in shared_dependencies.json. Security functions (create_access_token, decode_token, hash_password, verify_password) should be in app/core/security.py. The get_current_user dependency goes in app/core/dependencies.py.\n\nLet me know if you have any questions about the architecture!", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:12:40.815488"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/README.md", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:14:20.514258"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/.env.example", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:14:25.888524"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/requirements.txt", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:25:48.963521"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/Dockerfile.backend", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:25:58.105409"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "New file available: output/shared_dependencies.json", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:35:59.338130"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/Dockerfile.frontend", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:36:18.941964"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "Hi! I've reviewed your backend implementation against the feature_list. Great work overall - the code is clean and well-structured. I have two questions about deviations from the feature_list specs:\n\n1. **Login by username vs email (ISSUE-001, HIGH)**: Feature list F-002 says 'POST /api/auth/login accepts email and password', but your LoginRequest schema and auth_router use username. Was this intentional? The feature_list explicitly requires email-based login. Could you update LoginRequest to use email and change the auth_router login query to filter by User.email?\n\n2. **Duplicate registration returns 400 vs 409 (ISSUE-002, MEDIUM)**: Feature list F-001 says 'Duplicate email returns 409 Conflict', but your auth_router returns HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST. Could you change this to HTTP_409_CONFLICT for both duplicate username and duplicate email?\n\nOther observations (these are fine, just noting):\n- Your flat file structure (models.py, schemas.py, auth.py) instead of subdirectories is simpler and works well for this project size. I've updated shared_dependencies.json to match.\n- Your 3-value enums (low/medium/high for priority, todo/in_progress/done for status) match the feature_list correctly.\n- The DashboardStats endpoint is a nice addition not in my original architecture.\n- Using bcrypt directly instead of passlib is fine.\n\nI've updated shared_dependencies.json v1.1.0 to reflect the actual implementation structure. Please address issues 1 and 2 when you can.", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:36:47.143289"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/README.md", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:37:34.985791"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/.github/workflows/ci.yml", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:37:55.871938"}, {"from": "qa", "message": "New file available: output/src/backend/app/main.py", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:39:17.667591"}, {"from": "qa", "message": "New file available: output/tests/backend/conftest.py", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:41:13.058912"}, {"from": "devops", "message": "New file available: output/devops/README.md", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:43:34.726518"}, {"from": "reviewer", "message": "REVIEWER: Final confirmation check. Are you done with all deliverables? Two known issues flagged by architect: (1) Login uses username instead of email (F-002 requires email), (2) Duplicate registration returns 400 instead of 409 (F-001 requires 409). Are these fixed or pending? Please confirm completion status.", "urgent": true, "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:49:55.451669"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "ARCHITECTE follow-up: I see the 2 issues I flagged earlier haven't been addressed yet. Just a reminder in case you missed my earlier message:\n\n**ISSUE-001 (HIGH) - Login by email, not username:**\nFeature list F-002 says: 'POST /api/auth/login accepts email and password'. Currently both backend and frontend use username.\n\nFiles to change:\n- `app/schemas.py`: Change `LoginRequest` to have `email: str` instead of `username: str`\n- `app/routers/auth_router.py` line 46: Change `User.username == login_data.username` to `User.email == login_data.email`\n- `output/src/frontend/src/components/Login.jsx`: Change username field to email field\n- `output/src/frontend/src/api.js`: Login payload should send `{email, password}` instead of `{username, password}`\n- Update tests in `test_auth.py` accordingly\n\n**ISSUE-002 (MEDIUM) - 409 for duplicates:**\n- `app/routers/auth_router.py` lines 21 and 28: Change `HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST` to `HTTP_409_CONFLICT`\n- Update tests that check for 400 on duplicate registration to expect 409\n\nThese are required by the feature_list acceptance criteria. Let me know if you have questions or disagree with these changes.", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:50:45.691249"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "ARCHITECTE: Great work fixing the backend issues! Both ISSUE-001 and ISSUE-002 are resolved on the backend side. However, the frontend Login.jsx still uses username:\n\n- Line 6: `const [username, setUsername] = useState('')`\n- Line 15: `authAPI.login({ username, password })` \u2014 but the backend now expects `{ email, password }`\n- Line 29: `placeholder=\"Username\"` should be `placeholder=\"Email\"`\n- Line 29: `type=\"text\"` should be `type=\"email\"` for proper validation\n\nThis will cause a runtime error since the backend LoginRequest now expects an `email` field, not `username`. The frontend will send `{username, password}` but the backend expects `{email, password}`.\n\nCould you update Login.jsx to use email instead of username? The changes are:\n1. Rename `username`/`setUsername` state to `email`/`setEmail`\n2. Change `authAPI.login({ username, password })` to `authAPI.login({ email, password })`\n3. Change input type to `email` and placeholder to `Email`", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:51:32.791423"}, {"from": "architecte", "message": "New file available: output/shared_dependencies.json", "timestamp": "2026-03-26T20:54:32.948958"}]
